<REFEX REG08-TYPE="common" EMPHATIC="no" HEAD="nominal" CASE="plain">the volcano</REFEX>
<REFEX REG08-TYPE="common" EMPHATIC="yes" HEAD="nominal" CASE="plain">the volcano itself</REFEX>
</ALT-REFEX>
</REF>
 borders the Monturaqui Basin, which is draped with the large debris avalanche deposit. Escondida mining currently has a network of roads covering this area, from beneath which they pump ground water for use at the nearby copper mine. The southern margin of the deposit is bordered by the Antofagasta to Salta trans-Andean railway, although this is rarely used.</PARAGRAPH>
